---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
import MessageBlock from '../../components/MessageBlock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Brand Identity · Positioning"
  description="Who Increments is, who it serves, what it replaces, and what makes it different — in one formal statement."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Brand Identity · 04"
    title="Positioning Statement"
    italicWord="Positioning"
    lede="Positioning is the single sentence that says who we are, who we serve, what we replace, and what makes us different. If it's wrong, everything downstream — messaging, hiring, pricing — goes slightly off."
  />

  <Section title="The statement" kicker="Memorize this one">
    <MessageBlock label="Formal positioning statement" variant="lime">
      <p>
        <strong>For operator-founders and small-to-mid enterprise buyers</strong> who
        need custom software built with real speed and real quality —
        <strong>Increments is a premium engineering studio</strong> that replaces
        traditional agencies, offshore dev shops, and full-team hiring — by
        shipping working software in <em>7-day prototypes</em>, staying
        <em>founder-direct</em>, and <em>locking pricing for 24 months</em> so
        founders can plan without surprises.
      </p>
    </MessageBlock>

    <p>
      That's one sentence with five components. Each is deliberately chosen —
      each is what makes Increments not-an-agency and not-an-offshore-shop.
      The sections below unpack each component.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Who we are" kicker="Component 01 · Category">
    <div class="positioning-row">
      <div class="positioning-claim">
        <span class="positioning-label">We are</span>
        <p>A <em>premium engineering studio</em>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="positioning-detail">
        <p>
          Not an agency (which implies account managers, client rosters, and
          margins on top of labor). Not an offshore dev shop (which implies
          cheap rates and no ownership). Not a staffing firm (which places
          bodies and walks away).
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Studio</strong> signals craft. <strong>Engineering</strong>
          signals depth. <strong>Premium</strong> signals we know what we're
          worth and won't compete on price.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Who we serve" kicker="Component 02 · Audience">
    <div class="positioning-row">
      <div class="positioning-claim">
        <span class="positioning-label">We serve</span>
        <p><em>Operator-founders</em> and <em>small-to-mid enterprise</em> buyers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="positioning-detail">
        <p>
          Operator-founders are running something — a product, a business,
          a team. They have taste, speed, and a pain. They need engineering
          firepower without the ramp time of hiring.
        </p>
        <p>
          Small-to-mid enterprise buyers (Head of Product, VP Engineering at
          companies between 50–500 employees) need external engineering for
          defined projects without adding to permanent headcount.
        </p>
        <p>
          We don't serve: pure procurement buyers at Fortune 500s, agencies
          looking to white-label cheap labor, or any client whose first
          question is <em>"what's your hourly rate?"</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="What we replace" kicker="Component 03 · Competition">
    <div class="replacement-grid">
      <article class="replacement-card">
        <span class="replacement-kicker">Replaces</span>
        <h4>Traditional agencies</h4>
        <p>$100K–$500K. 6–12 month timelines. Account managers in the middle. Endless change-orders.</p>
        <span class="replacement-vs">vs.</span>
        <p class="replacement-us">We ship a prototype in 7 days. No account managers. Locked scope, locked price.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="replacement-card">
        <span class="replacement-kicker">Replaces</span>
        <h4>Offshore dev shops</h4>
        <p>Cheap rates. No ownership. Screenshots that break in production. Time-zone roulette.</p>
        <span class="replacement-vs">vs.</span>
        <p class="replacement-us">Senior engineering. We own the work end-to-end. Your prototype runs in production.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="replacement-card">
        <span class="replacement-kicker">Replaces</span>
        <h4>Full-team hiring</h4>
        <p>6–18 month ramp. Benefits, management overhead. Wrong-hire risk. Permanent headcount.</p>
        <span class="replacement-vs">vs.</span>
        <p class="replacement-us">Senior team plugged in on day one. Pay for the project, not the payroll.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="What makes us different" kicker="Component 04 · Proof points">
    <ul class="proof-list">
      <li>
        <strong>7-day prototype.</strong> Working software in your hands before
        any contract is signed. If it doesn't convince you, there's no deal.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Founder-direct.</strong> You talk to the person building your
        software. No layers, no account managers, no "we'll circle back."
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Locked pricing · 24 months.</strong> The price we quote is the
        price you pay — protected against any future rate increase for 24
        months.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Free audit, then decide.</strong> We review your existing
        codebase or product at no cost. If there's no fit, we say so directly.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Real references, real work.</strong> Freeletics. Abwaab. Every
        case study is a founder you can call.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Anti-positioning" kicker="What we are NOT">
    <Callout variant="warning" title="If it describes us, we're off-brand.">
      <ul class="anti-list">
        <li>We are <strong>not</strong> the cheapest option.</li>
        <li>We are <strong>not</strong> a staffing or body-shop firm.</li>
        <li>We are <strong>not</strong> a "your-idea-our-team" SaaS builder on a fixed template.</li>
        <li>We are <strong>not</strong> a Fortune-500 enterprise consultancy with tiered pricing matrices.</li>
        <li>We are <strong>not</strong> a co-founder / equity-for-work arrangement.</li>
        <li>We are <strong>not</strong> a no-code, low-code, or AI-generated-code shop.</li>
      </ul>
    </Callout>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .positioning-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .positioning-claim {
    background: var(--color-surface-card-deep);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brand-lime);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-xl) var(--radius-xl) 0;
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-14) var(--space-14);
  }

  .positioning-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10.5px;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-bold);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .positioning-claim p {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-heavy);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-text-strong);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .positioning-claim em {
    font-family: var(--font-editorial);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
  }

  .positioning-detail p {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .positioning-detail p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
  }

  .positioning-detail em {
    font-family: var(--font-editorial);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
  }

  .replacement-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-7);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  .replacement-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-14) var(--space-14);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .replacement-kicker {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-bold);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-state-danger);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .replacement-card h4 {
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-heavy);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--color-text-strong);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .replacement-card p {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text-mute);
  }

  .replacement-vs {
    display: block;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-editorial);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
  }

  .replacement-us {
    color: var(--color-text-body) !important;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-medium);
    font-size: 13.5px !important;
  }

  .proof-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .proof-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .proof-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 9px;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    background: var(--color-brand-lime);
    border-radius: 2px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-icon-tile);
  }

  .anti-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .anti-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .anti-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 8px;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--color-state-danger);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .positioning-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .replacement-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
